This paper proposes a new method for graph representation learning using differentiable pooling, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. The paper focuses on improving graph classification, which is a task that falls under the categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also uses graph neural networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing, falling under the categories of computer vision, natural language processing, and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
